Hurricane is two-card draw poker, deuces wild, played as high/low; aces, deuces play both high and low.

This is an implementation of the game using Java and Prolog.
The game rules and artificial intelligence engine uses tuProlog (also known as 2p) from the University of Bologna.

To run the game, open a command-prompt (terminal) window and navigate to the out sub-folder, containing the JAR files. 
Enter one the following command:
  
    java -jar HurricanePoker.jar

For more information about the game, see the *.txt files in the src sub-folder.
  
Also see this WordPress blog article:
  
  http://rickrutt.wordpress.com/2012/01/21/playing-poker-with-prolog-and-java/
